main event: A witness observed a UFO hovering above the treetops for about 10 minutes in Newington, Connecticut on October 7, 1956.
interesting points: The UFO disappeared without sound or smoke,The witness, Thomas Warren, was a real estate agent,The sighting was documented with a letter sent to the Air Force,The photographs accompanying the report were considered too old to evaluate,The report contains insufficient data for evaluation and suggests the object may have been a balloon or astronomical.
witness description: Thomas Warren, a real estate agent
